## Description

#### Implements
Implements the `getRoomByName` method of `CasinoInterface`.

#### Overrides
`N/A`

#### Purpose
Provides a way to retrieve a specific `PokerRoom` by its unique name. This is useful for scenarios where rooms are accessed by their identifiers instead of their index.

#### Events
- `N/A`

#### Requirements
- The `name` parameter must match the name of an existing room.

---

## Casino - The class this method belongs to.

---

## Parameters
| Parameter Name | Type     | Default Value | Description                                |
|----------------|----------|---------------|--------------------------------------------|
| `name`         | `string` | `N/A`         | The unique name of the room to retrieve.   |

---

## Returns
| Type                  | Description                                |
|-----------------------|--------------------------------------------|
| `PokerRoomInterface`  | The `PokerRoom` with the specified name.   |
| `undefined`           | Returns `undefined` if no room with the specified name exists. |

---

## Throws
| Error Type    | Description                                |
|---------------|--------------------------------------------|
| `None`        | This method does not throw exceptions.    |

---

## Usage
This method retrieves a room by its name. If no room matches the specified name, it returns `undefined`.

---

## Examples
### Basic Example:
```typescript
const casino = new Casino();
casino.createRoom({ name: "Room1", tableSize: 6, smallBlind: 10, bigBlind: 20 });
const room = casino.getRoomByName("Room1");
console.log(room); // Outputs the details of "Room1"
```